      • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

        Not sure why Gomez didn't start. Goetze, as usual, did nothing of note in the striking role. I feel Loew uses the false 9 way too much. When used as a novelty, it can work because it messes up positioning of CBs & CMs when implemented well. Most of the time, however, it isn't that successful. The 4-time German player of the year (who also happens to have created the most chances by a country mile during the league season) had nobody to set up despite being in ideal positions. Gomez has scored 15 goals and assisted 2 in his last 20 matches for club and country and is every bit the #9 Germany call out for. I just don't see how anybody would think Goetze is a better option. Ukraine had chances to level it today despite Germany's dominance and that was partly down to having no real striking threat. Loads of shots, yes, but many were speculative efforts. The German defence isn't good enough to hold out at 1-0 and a better attacking side would've made them pay.
